The article is a statement issued on May 15, 2018, which sends greetings and best wishes to Muslims around the world observing Ramadan. It highlights the significance of Ramadan in the Muslim faith, including fasting, acts of charity, prayer, and reading the Quran. The statement emphasizes the importance of self-reflection and spiritual growth during this holy month. It also acknowledges the contributions of Muslims to the religious diversity in American society and the protection of religious liberty under the Constitution. The statement concludes by expressing hope for a blessed month and wishing "Ramadan Mubarak" (a blessed Ramadan).